      <translation>
         <line n="a1">
            <tr litRef="hackstein1995" pageRange="78"/>
            <tr>Meanwhile however [he ...] to the minister Kalendrasura ... now the name amongst those who are zealous [is] Dhaṃne </tr>
         </line>
         <line n="a2">
            <tr>by name was my disciple Artadhana. By name however [there were] seven disciples. </tr>
         </line>
         <line n="a3">
            <tr>... the dharma, in this retinue, the shallow and the deep manner [and] afterwards the beings ... </tr>
         </line>
         <line n="a4">
            <tr>Thus [he] spoke like a Buddha. "We, O God! are witnesses to this thing. </tr>
         </line>
         <line n="a5">
            <tr litRef="thomas1957" pageRange="236"/>
            <tr>The vassal kings of the father-king. When they burnt the brahmin woman ... and pulled [her] out of the fire. </tr>
         </line>
         <line n="a6">
            <tr litRef="thomas1979b" pageRange="51"/>
            <tr>... away. These four kings now preserve the world. [i.e. become cakravartins.] </tr>
         </line>
         <line n="b1">
            <tr litRef="thomas1979b" pageRange="58"/>
            <tr>Brahma is now the best of all gods. When my brother put out [my] eyes with violence... </tr>
         </line>
         <line n="b1 b2">
            <tr litRef="thomas1957" pageRange="235"/>
         </line>
         <line n="b2">
            <tr>Thereupon he spoke a word to me. He who is now Indra, lord of gods ... </tr>
         </line>
         <line n="b3">
            <tr litRef="thomas1957" pageRange="228"/>
            <tr>Devadatta was my brother at that time, [and] caused him to forget ... </tr>
         </line>
         <line n="b4">
            <tr>[were] ... the rākṣasas. Thereupon for the first time they gave me the cintamaṇi-jewel. </tr>
         </line>
         <line n="b5">
            <tr litRef="hackstein1995" pageRange="90, 163"/>
            <tr>in these regions. 16. In these same eight regions however these rākṣasas came to me. </tr>
         </line>
         <line n="b6">
            <tr>He paints these great figures of men upon this earth. </tr>
         </line>
      </translation>
